    <title>The Parental Leave (EU Directive) Regulations 2013: impact assessment</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary></summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assesses the impact from draft regulations (URN 12/1284) that extend UK parental leave legislation to comply with EU Directive 2010/18 on Parental Leave by 2013. It intends to implement the Parental Leave Directive to encourage shared parenting and maintain attachment to the labour market whilst minimising burdens to business. This supports the proposed new system of flexible parental leave due to be introduced in 2015.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
